703894f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - Bay 17th Street
703894f-a.text:
1755-1763 Cropsey Ave., north side, at the N.E. corner of Bay 17th
Street. The house on the extreme right, is 1765 Cropsey Ave.
January 11, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

703896f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - Bay 17th Street
703896f-a.text:
(1)
Cropsey Ave., south side, between Bay 17th and 19th Streets. A
view of a number of homes and cottages, for children under the jurisdiction
of the N.Y. Children's Aid Society. It is the Children'e Summer Home.
April 27, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, another angle.
April 27, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same, another angle.
April 27, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

703897f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - Bay 17th Street
703897f-a.text:
Cropsey Ave., south side, between Bay 17 and Bay 19 Streets. A
view of the gate house to the summer home of the N.Y. Children's Aid Society.
April 27, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

703895f-b.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - Bay 17th Street
703895f-b.text:
Cropsey Ave., south side, between Bay 17th and Bay 19th Streets,
showing the summer home of the New York Children's Aid Secietyg which
was founded in 1881 by Andros H. Stone.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Ardbruster Colleetion.
The same, showing a rear view of other buildings, belonging to the
Society.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
The same, showing another rear view, from Bay 19th Street.
October 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
